        <p>
            For those DMTs which are irreversible it is not only necessary to wait for drug levels to be 
            ‘sub-therapeutic’, but also for natural reconstitution of the immune system (e.g. production of 
            new immune cells).  For reversible DMTs, effects are lost once the drug is ‘washed out’ (Figure 1).  
