        <p>
            Patients with active MS who switch to fingolimod or natalizumab from other DMTs are likely to experience similar reductions in their use of healthcare resources. Of patients who switched to fingolimod, 68% were free of relapses. That was compared with 69% of patients who switched to natalizumab. The cohorts also recorded similar rates of hospitalizations and corticosteroid use, down significantly from the year before the switch (p < 0.01)<sup>36</sup>.
        </p>
